Junction Hill Hornet Athletics
September 8 at 5:46 PM ·

Great day to be a Hornet! Girls A-Team battled Fairview to a 1-1 TIE after 12 grueling innings! Boys A-Team came back from a 6-1 deficit to win with a walk-off single by Parker Bell for a 9-8 win! Winning pitcher was also Parker Bell! Both B-Teams played, learned, and got some experience under their belts to help them for games this Friday vs Howell Valley. Good job to all and GOOOOOOO HORNETS!

post_text: Today we presented our 2019-2020 coaches with a small gift to thank them for all of their hard work and dedication to our athletes this year. We were truly blessed to have each and every one of them. Please leave a message in the comment section and let them know how much they are appreciated.

post_text:
We’d like to recognize Liz Bolander at this time. Liz has been involved with the booster club for several years and has served as the president for the last 9. Liz gives freely of her time and always has the best interest of the student-athletes and coaches in mind. Liz has spent countless hours planning banquets, fundraisers, preparing and working at home athletic events and basically doing anything she can to provide a better opportunity for the kids at Junction Hill. Liz is retiring from the booster club at the end of this year and will be greatly missed. She has been a great leader and an even better team player. We want Liz to know how very much she is appreciated.

Liz will be receiving a special delivery with a gift certificate later this week from the Junction Hill Booster Club . Please joining us in thanking Liz for all she has done for Junction Hill School over the years.
